  "title": "Registered Replication Report of ERN/Pe Psychometrics",
  "description": "A registered replication report investigating the psychometric properties of error-related negativity (ERN) and error positivity (Pe) components derived from EEG recordings. Raw EGI MFF files were processed using EEGLAB, with task-specific events recoded into response-locked and stimulus-locked ERN/Pe-relevant event labels, and subsequently converted to BIDS format for standardized data sharing and reproducibility.",
  "methods_description": "EEG data were acquired using EGI systems and recorded in MFF format. Raw files were imported and processed using EEGLAB, with task-specific events recoded into response-locked and stimulus-locked event labels relevant to ERN/Pe analysis. Data were then exported to BIDS format.",
